   Women's Health Research Program

   Women's Health Research Program
     __________________________________________________________________

   The Women’s Health Research Program is part of the Institute for
   Clinical and Epidemiological Research (ICER), an umbrella organization
   for a diverse group of health services research entities and their
   activities, at the Veterans Affairs Medical Center in Durham, North
   Carolina.

   Our Mission

   The Women’s Health Research Program’s mission is to conduct research
   aimed at enhancing the knowledge and quality of women veteran’s health.

   Who We Are

   The Program is comprised of an interdisciplinary team of investigators
   dedicated to women’s health research such as biostatisticians,
   epidemiologist, psychologists, and physicians in the fields of internal
   medicine, obstetrics & gynecology, and psychiatry.

   What We Do

   The Program conducts research pertinent to the health of women veterans
   which has included breast cancer, cardiology, osteoporosis, hepatitis
   C, hormone replacement therapy, self-rated health, and sexual trauma.

   Women’s Health Fellowships
   are available to M.D. applicants who are board eligible or certified in
   internal medicine, gynecology, or psychiatry.


   For more information, contact:

